@startuml
title game-lib entities: entity architecture

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
hide circle
hide empty members

package "Core foundation" {
  abstract class BaseNode
  abstract class GameEntityLifeCycle {
    +_setup(...)
    +_update(...)
    +_destroy(...)
  }

  interface MoveableEntity
  interface RotatableEntityAPI
}

package "Entity runtime model" {
  class GameEntity {
    +group
    +mesh
    +materials
    +compoundMeshes
    --
    +bodyDesc
    +body
    +colliderDesc
    +colliderDescs
    +colliders
    +physicsAttached
    --
    +behaviors
    +behaviorRefs
    +transformStore
    --
    +add(part)
    +use(descriptor, options)
    +runAction(action)
    +action(action)
    +onCollision(callback)
    +clone()
  }

  interface EntityDebugInfo
  interface CollisionHandlerDelegate
}

BaseNode <|-- GameEntity
GameEntityLifeCycle <|.. GameEntity
MoveableEntity <|.. GameEntity
RotatableEntityAPI <|.. GameEntity
EntityDebugInfo <|.. GameEntity

package "Builders and creation pipeline" {
  class "createEntity(...)" as CreateEntity <<factory>>
  class EntityBuilder {
    +build()
  }
  abstract class EntityMeshBuilder
  abstract class EntityCollisionBuilder

  class EntityFactory {
    +register(type, creator)
    +createFromBlueprint(blueprint)
  }

  class "createEntityFactory(...)" as CreateEntityFactory <<factory>>
  class EntityBlueprint
}

CreateEntity --> EntityBuilder : generic construction path
EntityBuilder --> EntityMeshBuilder : optional mesh builder
EntityBuilder --> EntityCollisionBuilder : optional collision builder
EntityFactory --> EntityBlueprint : reads
EntityFactory --> GameEntity : creates
CreateEntityFactory --> GameEntity : clones / generates

package "Composition parts" {
  class "mesh-factories.ts" as MeshFactories <<module>>
  class "collision-factories.ts" as CollisionFactories <<module>>
  class CollisionComponent
  class BehaviorDescriptor
  class BehaviorRef
  interface Action
  class TransformState
  class AssetManager
}

GameEntity --> CollisionComponent : add(...)
GameEntity --> BehaviorRef : stores
BehaviorRef --> BehaviorDescriptor : wraps
GameEntity --> Action : runAction / action
GameEntity --> TransformState : owns
Action --> TransformState : writes intents

package "Concrete entity families" {
  class ZylemBox
  class ZylemSphere
  class ZylemActor
  class ZylemZone
  class ZylemParticleSystem

  class "primitive factories\ncreateBox / createSphere /\ncreatePlane / createRect /\ncreateCone / createCylinder /\ncreatePill / createPyramid / ..." as PrimitiveFactories <<factory>>
}

GameEntity <|-- ZylemBox
GameEntity <|-- ZylemSphere
GameEntity <|-- ZylemActor
GameEntity <|-- ZylemZone
GameEntity <|-- ZylemParticleSystem

PrimitiveFactories --> ZylemBox : creates
PrimitiveFactories --> ZylemSphere : creates
PrimitiveFactories --> MeshFactories : compose mesh parts
PrimitiveFactories --> CollisionFactories : compose collision parts

ZylemActor --> AssetManager : model / texture loading
ZylemZone ..|> CollisionHandlerDelegate

package "Runtime collaborators" {
  class StageEntityDelegate
  class ZylemStage
  class ZylemWorld
  interface BehaviorSystem
}

ZylemStage --> StageEntityDelegate : owns entity runtime
StageEntityDelegate --> BaseNode : spawns / traverses
StageEntityDelegate --> GameEntity : tracks / registers
StageEntityDelegate --> BehaviorSystem : auto-registers by behavior key
BehaviorSystem --> GameEntity : updates linked entities
ZylemWorld --> GameEntity : attach bodies / colliders
ZylemWorld --> CollisionHandlerDelegate : dispatch delegate callbacks

note right of GameEntity
Central composition root for gameplay content.

Responsibilities:
- visual state via mesh / group / materials
- physics descriptors and runtime body refs
- child-node composition from BaseNode
- actions and buffered transform intent
- behavior attachment through descriptor refs
end note

note bottom of GameEntity
Two behavior-related concepts coexist:
- `behaviors`: legacy / ECS-style registrations
- `behaviorRefs`: descriptor-driven attachments from `use(...)`

That split is important when reading the runtime.
end note

note bottom of EntityBuilder
Builder path converts entity options into:
- materials
- mesh geometry
- body/collider descriptors
- final entity setup

This is the main reusable construction pipeline.
end note

note right of PrimitiveFactories
Simple shapes follow a strong
composition-over-inheritance pattern:

factory -> GameEntity subclass
       -> mesh part(s)
       -> collision part(s)
end note

note right of ZylemActor
`ZylemActor` is the heavyweight model-backed entity:
- asset loading
- animation delegates
- richer collision strategies
end note

note right of ZylemZone
`ZylemZone` highlights the delegate-based
collision path used for sensor-like entities
with enter / held / exit semantics.
end note

legend right
|= Area |= Purpose |
| Entity runtime model | main object graph and capabilities |
| Builders and creation pipeline | how entities are constructed |
| Composition parts | reusable pieces attached to entities |
| Concrete entity families | primitives and higher-level entities |
| Runtime collaborators | stage/world systems that activate entities |
endlegend

@enduml
